cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with training a Deep Network to predict a 3D pose from an image using synthetic images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a network to infer the 3D pose, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper demonstrates its approach on datasets for object pose estimation and hand pose estimation, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) as well.
